                     <br />
                     <br />
                      <b>Checking the Source</b>
                      <br/>
                        It's important to be aware that images of Tweets or posts can easily be fabricated.  As this is a post on Facebook, any Tweet by itself is not a sign of false information as Tweets cannot be shared directly.
                      <br/>
                        Here, as a Member of Parliament is saying something so controversial, this is a sign that the original source should be checked.   A quick Google search should help you find the Tweet to see if Chris Minns actually did post this.
                        <br />
                        <br />
                        <b>Understanding the who the Author is</b>
                        <br />
                        A quick google search will show results that this Facebook page has previously been caught out for sharing fake photos.
                        <br/>
                        The actual Facebook page is predominantly sharing meme's.  This suggests that there's a high chance that this post is satire and shouldn't be believed.
